{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KMeyHwX39L1RzvgcQm8gEs","type":"tool_result","content":"   650→| Flag | Description |\n   651→|------|-------------|\n   652→| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   653→| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n   654→| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n   655→| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n   656→\n   657→Must be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\n   658→when `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n   659→\n   660→### `cloche status`\n   661→\n   662→```\n   663→cloche status <run-id>\n   664→```\n   665→\n   666→Shows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n   667→\n   668→### `cloche list`\n   669→\n   670→```\n   671→cloche list [flags]\n   672→```\n   673→\n   674→Lists runs for the current project directory. Pass `--all` to show runs across all projects.\n   675→Results can be filtered by state, project, issue, or limited to a fixed number.\n   676→\n   677→| Flag | Description |\n   678→|------|-------------|\n   679→| `--all` | Show runs from all projects (default: current project only). |\n   680→| `--project, -p DIR` | Filter by project directory. |\n   681→| `--state, -s STATE` | Filter by run state (`pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`). |\n   682→| `--limit, -n NUM` | Limit the number of results returned. |\n   683→| `--issue, -i ID` | Filter by issue/task ID. |\n   684→\n   685→### `cloche logs`\n   686→\n   687→```\n   688→cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n   689→```"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cf91f3d9-a304-4a52-a199-e74adbb9c824","uuid":"dc9f5e0d-f277-4e91-89aa-4a4c881d5314","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n\nMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\nwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n\n### `cloche status`\n\n```\ncloche status <run-id>\n```\n\nShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n\n### `cloche list`\n\n```\ncloche list [flags]\n```\n\nLists runs for the current project directory. Pass `--all` to show runs across all projects.\nResults can be filtered by state, project, issue, or limited to a fixed number.\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--all` | Show runs from all projects (default: current project only). |\n| `--project, -p DIR` | Filter by project directory. |\n| `--state, -s STATE` | Filter by run state (`pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`). |\n| `--limit, -n NUM` | Limit the number of results returned. |\n| `--issue, -i ID` | Filter by issue/task ID. |\n\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n```","numLines":40,"startLine":650,"totalLines":920}}}
