{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012CpNvQAz8fcZGqnF3nyAPQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The changes are internal plumbing: the agent runner now includes the failed step name in `MsgError` messages, and the daemon's `trackRun` uses those to populate `run.ErrorMessage` via `run.Fail()`. The existing documentation already describes:\n\n- `error_message` field in the gRPC protocol (in the implementation plan)\n- `ErrorMessage` on the `Run` domain type (in the implementation plan)\n- `cloche status` shows \"state, active steps, and per-step results\" (in USAGE.md)\n\nThe `Fail()` method and `ErrorMessage` field already existed before this change — the code change just wires them up properly. The user-facing behavior of `cloche status` hasn't changed its documented interface; it still shows state and step results. The error message was already part of the documented protocol.\n\nNo documentation updates are needed — the existing docs already describe the `error_message` field and the status output. The change is purely an internal bug fix that correctly populates fields that were already documented.\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2535,"cache_read_input_tokens":23027,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2535},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cf91f3d9-a304-4a52-a199-e74adbb9c824","uuid":"5e11ecf2-53f8-4916-81a7-cf8ee62c5fd1"}
